1. heat a pan
2. add 3tbsp butter
3. add all the onion
4. when the onions are golden add both all the garlic paste and chilly paste
5. after the oil seprates add all the cpcicum
6. add all the cauliflower, potato, grated beetroot and greenpeas slowly
7. mix and mash the bhaji
8. after 5 mins add all the chopped tomatoes 
9. after 3 mins ad the coriander powder, turmeric powder, pavbhaji masala and some salt
10. mix all th stuff and add some water after 2 mins
11. let it boil for 6-7 mins
serve hot with half a lemon and two pavs toasted on a pan  